					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A kabbalistic work from the school of Isaac Luria, probably redacted by Jacob Ẓemah, with additions by Ḥayim Vital.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Adam yashar</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">אדם ישר</title>
							<note>
								<p>Contains additions and glosses by Moses ben Mordecai Zacuto (marked as Kol Rama"z) and Nathan ben Reuben Shapira.</p>
								<p>On this treatise see further <ref target="Avivi_2008" type="page">729-731</ref>, vol. 2.</p>
							</note>
							<locus from="1r" to="210v"/>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/18664254">Ẓemaḥ, Jacob ben Ḥayyim, active 17th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/18664254">צמח, יעקב בן חיים</persName>
							</author>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">Vital, Ḥayyim ben Joseph, 1542-1620</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">ויטל, חיים בן יוסף, 1542-1620</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Adam_yashar_1885"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">לסיים מלאכת הספר הזה יום ו' עשרים יום לח' תמוז יה"ל שנת אם <date calendar="Hebrew">י'ת'מ'ה'מ'ה'</date> [=תק] חכה לו אני הצעיר מעבדי השם ב"ה <name type="person" role="scribe">שלמה בן לא"א אברהם רופא</name> יזיי"א.<locus n="210r"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 18th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>210 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>245</height>
										<width>180</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>180</height>
										<width>135</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>210 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and 5 at the end). Folio 1 is a paper flyleaf.</p>
									<p>Original Hebrew foliation, left-hand upper corner of each recto.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 16 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Slightly stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="28 36" writtenLines="28 36">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Headings and initial words in larger square characters.</p>
									<p>Additions and comments in the margin.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
